President Donald J. Trump spoke with President Moon Jae-in of South Korea to discuss preparations for their upcoming engagements with North Korea. They both stressed the importance of learning from past mistakes and pledged to maintain maximum pressure on North Korea. They agreed that concrete actions, not words, are crucial for achieving permanent denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. President Trump reiterated his intention to meet with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un by the end of May. Both leaders expressed cautious optimism and emphasized that North Korea can have a brighter future if it chooses the right path.